column5: I managed to get out to my camp a few times and do some pretty gnarly bass fishing.  On average we got abotu 40 fish a day, with some days over 60.  I made a vid with some pics and short videos!
Right on buddy, good highlight reel, what a lake that is!!!  A couple more weeks we'll be cranking that tune during predawn runs up the hwy.
Sounds like a great time hooking into those bronzes Thanks for sharing the video Dr!!! Leechman
77mm of rain back home... if i was in the soo i'd be at the snowdrift river right now.
I saw...was watching the charts...reminds me of the fall of 2007 when we got that gully washer in september
Crazy!  Looks like a pretty awesome lake!
WOW! Some nice smallies there for sure. Great rockin vid, love the motorhead!
